{"DESQUAMATE":[{"def":"To peel off in the form of scales; to scale off, as the skin in certain diseases.","pos":""}],"DESQUAMATION":[{"def":"The separation or shedding of the cuticle or epidermis in the form of flakes or scales; exfoliation, as of bones.","pos":""},{"def":"Of, pertaining to, or attended with, desquamation.","pos":""}],"DESQUAMATORY":[{"def":"An instrument formerly used in removing the laminæ of exfoliated bones.","pos":""}]}